            </funcprototype>
        </funcsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsect1 xml:id="parameters"><title>Parameters</title>
        <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><parameter>d</parameter></term>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Specifies double precision value to break into a pair of unsigned integers.
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsect1>
    <refsect1 xml:id="description"><title>Description</title>
        <para>
            <function>unpackDouble2x32</function> returns a two-component unsigned integer vector
            representation of <parameter>d</parameter>. The bit-level representation of <parameter>d</parameter> is
            preserved. The first component of the returned vector contains
            the 32 least significant bits of the double; the second
            component consists the 32 most significant bits.
        </para>
    </refsect1>
